commit.message: Fix sorting on list-type fields when there is no default field value and values are None
Make document wider
Make docs page wider to accomodate code snippets
Move most documentation to the docs site
Add generated documentation
Update description
Add better test coverage of new Q 'never' option
Remove unnecessary commas
Change semantics of 'foo__in=[]' to return empty results. Refs #770
Use the new 'never' functionality in Q() to implement .none()
Refactor Q to simplify __init__ and allow reuse
Support Q objects that are guaranted to not return any results
'setup.py test' is deprecated. Use the new method to call tests
Let GetUserOofSettings work like other services, even though it only returns one item. Just use.get() to retrieve it
Refactor _get_elements() so we can re-use it in paging services and share error handling. Fixes an erro where ErrorTooManyObjectsOpened was not properly handled in a paging service.Refs #758
Add increase_poolsize(), complement of decrease_poolsize()
No need to limit queue. It's small, we may want to increase it dynamically, and other code handles the queue size
Fix flake8 after #768
Remove duplicate field. Was already defined in BaseMeetingItem
Add missing fields on MeetingResponse. Refs #769

Change docstring style to google (#768)

* Remove old docs

* Fix rest syntax

* Change docstring style to google

by running `pyment -o google -p False -t -w exchangelib`.
Also, ignore changes to `exchangelib/autodiscover/protocol.py` because 
of pyment bug.

* Remove empty sections

* Fix split lines
